content: Potential Mechanisms tell me Notes: Based on administrative records from the Washington State Impaired Driver Testing Program linked with administrative records from the Washington State Courts. In panel A, points represent averages, with fitted values based on local linear models in black lines. The vertical black lines represent the two legal thresholds at 0.08 and 0.15. The bin width is 0.002. Panel B is based on estimates from regression discontinuity models. The points represent estimates while the lines represent the end points of 95 percent confidence interval.
